orangelight.title: Refused to display 'https://library.princeton.edu/' in a frame because it set 'X-Frame-Options' to 'sameorigin'.

comments.body:
Also, when we match the feature flippers on staging to the ones on production (with the older Firestone Locator on), we do *not* see this bug, but the first item (the one with the bug) is in a different location on staging than it is in production.

Staging:
![The location of the broken object is "Architecture Library - Stacks"](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5d51624a5b89150001ae0b03/43fadd58-01f7-488f-9433-c5735a4a7047)

Production:
![The location of the broken object is "Architecture Library - Reserve 3-Hour"](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5d51624a5b89150001ae0b03/02938d8e-4e2d-407e-bec3-eeda729572cc)

The stackmap url comes from the `holdings_1display` in Solr (not from the bibdata availability response)

Production location in holdings_1display

```json
  "arch$res3hr": {
    "location_code": "arch$res3hr",
    "current_location": "Reserve 3-Hour",
    "current_library": "Architecture Library",
    "call_number": "HT166.I3",
    "call_number_browse": "HT166.I3",
    "temp_location_code": "arch$res3hr",
    "items": [same as staging]
  }
```

Staging holdings_1display

```json
  "22485327350006421": {
    "location_code": "arch$stacks",
    "location": "Stacks",
    "library": "Architecture Library",
    "call_number": "HT166.I3",
    "call_number_browse": "HT166.I3",
    "items": [same as production]
  }
```

It looks like this is one of the `missing_stackmap_reserves` locations, which returns the branch library's url - so, the link itself should be directly to https://library.princeton.edu/architecture, without going through stackmap.

pdc_discovery.title: One Solr node seems to be down

comments.body:
We could not get a new replica to work on the existing `pdc-discovery-production` collection. We tried deleting the existing replicas and re-creating them in `lib-solr-prod4/5/6` to no avail.

Instead we created a new Solr collection called `pdc-discovery-production-2` with two replicas and that worked perfectly. We then re-indexed the data by running the reindex rake task with SOLR-URL env pointing to `http://lib-solr8-prod.princeton.edu:8983/solr/pdc-discovery-production-2`. 

**UPDATE on Mar/2023** To create the new collection we do it via the Solr Admin "Add Collection". There is already a config set for `pdc-discovery-production` that we use to create the new one.

Once we confirmed the data was reindexed in `pdc-discovery-production-2` we **deleted** the old `pdc-discovery-production` collection and created an alias so that the new `pdc-discovery-production-2` collection is also known as `pdc-discovery-production`, this way the PDC discovery code and configuration does not need to be updated.

pdc_discovery.title: SolrCloud replica node lib-solr-prod6.princeton.edu is failing for Solr Collection pdc-discovery-production-2

comments.body:
Many, many thanks @hectorcorrea! An additional Solr Collection was created (`pdc-discovery-production-1`), and the Solr index was repopulated over a terminal session:

```bash

deploy@pdc-discovery-prod2:/opt/pdc_discovery/current$ SOLR_URL=http://lib-solr-prod6.princeton.edu:8983/solr/pdc-discovery-production-1/ bundle exec
rake index:research_data
```

The Solr Collection Alias was also replaced with one which now defaults exclusively for `pdc-discovery-production-1`:

```bash
deploy@pdc-discovery-prod2:/opt/pdc_discovery/current$ curl "http://lib-solr-prod6.princeton.edu:8983/solr/admin/collections?action=LISTALIASES"
{
  "responseHeader":{
    "status":0,
    "QTime":0},
  "aliases":{
    "catalog-alma-production":"catalog-alma-production2",
    "library-prod":"library-prod1",
    "special-collections-prod":"special-collections-prod2",
    "dss":"dss-production2",
    "catalog-alma-production-rebuild":"catalog-alma-production3",
    "lae-prod":"lae-prod3",
    "pdc-discovery-production":"pdc-discovery-production-1"},
  "properties":{}}
```

The final task for fully resolving this will be to ensure that `pdc-discovery-production-2`. However, it was proposed that this be delayed until tomorrow (when we can be certain that the migration incurred no problems).
